          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="0" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> The beautiful frosted FERNY<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(2.80)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10268'>steven "GIMLItheTANK" colby</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10268&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 25, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> The three will fail, and many fair things will fade and be forgotten.-Beauty is fading  rare 205, first set<br>
The small and weak suffer first from the white wizards powerful sorcery.- Sarumans Frost uncommon 135 first set<br>
As for ferny, he would sell anything to anybody, or make mischief for amusement.-Bill Ferny, rare 75 second set<br>
<br>
This article is meant to delve into the combo of these three cards. Ferny can cause many players mischief if they are not prepared for him. This is to give an insight into the combo and how to beat the combo.<br>
 First the cards in the combo:<br>
<br>
Beauty is Fading- cost 5<br>
Event<br>
Maneuver: Exert a Nazgul to discard a free peoples possession or free peoples condition. If you can spot no such card, discard an ally or companion (except the ring bearer) instead.<br>
<br>
Sarumans Frost- cost 2<br>
	Condition<br>
	Weather, spell: To play exert a isengard minion. Plays on a sit. Limit one per site. Each hobbit at this site is strength 2. Discard this condition at the end of the turn.<br>
<br>
Bill Ferny- cost 2<br>
Power-4<br>
Vitality-1<br>
Text: Nazgul are not roaming. <br>
The free peoples player may not assign a character to skirmish bill ferny. Discard bill ferny if underground.<br>
<br>
The goal of this deck is to get ferny versus the ring bearer. <br>
As it stands it would be an even match 4 power versus a 4 power. So whats the big deal frodo or sam take a wound or put on the one ring and take a burden. But--------- if you play ferny after you have played the frost on a site the hobbit is power 2 making fordo or sam a 2 power and allowing ferny to overwhelm him. Now the beauty is fading comes in when the ring bearer has a weapon(i.e. hobbit sword or sting) or condition (o elberoth, I totally misspelled that) that pumps up his vitality. Use the fading to discard it.<br>
<br>
This is how an actual game played out a month ago at a tournament in Lansdale, nj. <br>
First turn- the free peoples player grabs Aragorn. Gives Aragorn athelas, his sword. So far there is six in the twilight pool. He then drops boromir with the blade of gondor. Now theres 11. he moves to a site that add another two plus the five for the companions (frodo, Arwen and gimli started). For a total of 18 twilight pool. The minion side drops a urukhai rager I believe for 6. A sarumans frost for 2 and a exertion then the man to end it all ferny. The free peoples player assigns the rager to aragorn. The minion side assigns the ferny to frod overwhelming the hobbit since the free people player had no pump ups for hobbits in his hand. A first turn overwhelming.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Now what makes this combo so effective is that its a surprise. There are ways to beat it. And here are a few.<br>
<br>
1.	Bounders<br>
2.	hobbit stealth/intuition<br>
3.	a couple o elbereths (fading can kill it)<br>
4.	hobbit swords(fading can kill it)<br>
5.	the best way to avoid it is to use the best action in the game aimed archery. Rare legolas or aragorn with his bow and they can shoot down that pip squeak.<br>
<br>
<br>
I wrote this so as to help other people out who do not know of this combo. Recently I traded 3 extra fernys away to a top player. I knew of the combo and it didnt worry me. But I figured might as well let other people know of it since I cant find any listings of it. Its not a broken combo just one that relies on surprise, because how many decks do you know of that have frost in them? I hope I was of some help in preventing a loss to this combo.<br>
<br>
When you review this article please give insight into how I could of made it better. Thanks.<br>
